{
  "local_port": 56454,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How I make a call in Jio sim?",
  "response": "Making a call using your Jio SIM is a straightforward process. Whether you're using a smartphone or a feature phone, follow the steps below to initiate a call:\n\n### **For Smartphones:**\n\n#### **1. Ensure Your Jio SIM is Active:**\n- **Activation:** If you've recently inserted a new Jio SIM, ensure it's activated. Typically, Jio SIMs are activated within a few hours of purchase. You can check activation status by:\n  - Calling Jio Customer Care: Dial **198** (from your Jio number) or **1800 889 9999** (from any other number).\n  - Sending an SMS: Text `Available` to **199**.\n- **Recharge:** Ensure your Jio account has an active plan with sufficient balance or validity to make calls.\n\n#### **2. Insert the Jio SIM into Your Smartphone:**\n- Turn off your phone.\n- Insert the Jio SIM into the SIM slot (usually the primary slot) of your device.\n- Turn the phone back on and wait for it to recognize the SIM.\n\n#### **3. Configure Network Settings (If Needed):**\n- Most smartphones automatically configure network settings for Jio.\n- Ensure mobile data is turned on for better call quality (VoLTE).\n- To verify VoLTE is enabled:\n  - **Android:** Go to **Settings > Mobile Networks > Preferred network type** and ensure **LTE/VoLTE** is selected.\n  - **iPhone:** Go to **Settings > Cellular > Cellular Data Options > Voice & Data** and ensure **LTE** is selected.\n\n#### **4. Make a Call:**\n- **Dial the Number:**\n  - Open the **Phone** app.\n  - Enter the desired phone number or select a contact from your address book.\n  - Press the **Call** button (usually a green phone icon).\n- **Using Voice Assistants:**\n  - Activate Google Assistant or Siri and say, for example, \"Call [Contact Name].\"\n\n### **For Feature Phones:**\n\n#### **1. Ensure Your Jio SIM is Active:**\n- Follow the same activation steps as mentioned for smartphones.\n\n#### **2. Insert the Jio SIM into Your Feature Phone:**\n- Turn off the phone.\n- Insert the SIM into the SIM slot.\n- Turn the phone back on.\n\n#### **3. Make a Call:**\n- **Dial the Number:**\n  - Open the **Dial Pad**.\n  - Enter the desired phone number.\n  - Press the **Call** button (usually a green phone icon or the number **1**).\n- **Access Contacts:**\n  - Navigate to the **Contacts** menu.\n  - Select the desired contact and choose the **Call** option.\n\n### **Using JioCall App (For Smartphones & PCs):**\n\nJioCall allows you to make calls using your Jio number over the internet.\n\n#### **1. Download and Install JioCall:**\n- **For Smartphones:**\n  - **Android:** Visit the [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ni.ac.speaker) and search for **JioCall**.\n  - **iOS:** Due to app availability, check the [Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/) for Jio equivalents or use Jio\u2019s official recommendations.\n- **For PC:** Visit the [JioCall website](https://www.jio.com/call-profile/) for PC installation instructions.\n\n#### **2. Set Up JioCall:**\n- Open the **JioCall** app.\n- Sign in using your Jio number and verify it via OTP.\n- Follow on-screen instructions to complete the setup.\n\n#### **3. Make a Call:**\n- Enter the desired phone number or select a contact within the app.\n- Press the **Call** button to initiate the call.\n\n### **Troubleshooting Tips:**\n\n- **No Network Signal:**\n  - Ensure you're in an area with Jio network coverage.\n  - Try toggling the **Airplane Mode** on and off.\n  - Restart your phone.\n\n- **Unable to Make Calls:**\n  - Check if your Jio plan has call minutes available.\n  - Ensure that your phone's software is up to date.\n  - Contact Jio Customer Support if the issue persists.\n\n- **Poor Call Quality:**\n  - Ensure a strong network signal.\n  - If using VoLTE, make sure it's enabled.\n  - Switch to Wi-Fi calling if available.\n\n### **Contacting Jio Support:**\n\nIf you encounter persistent issues, you can reach out to Jio Customer Care:\n\n- **Call:** Dial **198** from your Jio number or **1800 889 9999** from any other number.\n- **Email:** Reach out via the [Jio Support Email](https://www.jio.com/support).\n- **Visit a Jio Store:** Locate the nearest Jio store through the [Jio Store Locator](https://www.jio.com/store-locator).\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to successfully make calls using your Jio SIM. If you continue to experience difficulties, contacting Jio\u2019s customer support is recommended for personalized assistance.",
